MICRORHOPALA. M'wrorhopala, Baly, Ann. 8⁶ Mag. Nat. Hist. 3rd ser. xiv. p. 268 (1864).

The insects entering into the present genus form a natural group, closely allied to Uroplata, but separated by the nearly plane interocular space and by the more regular oval form. The present species, four in number, inhabit North and Central America‚ one (M. salloei) being also found in Golombia.
